Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Relation/range

Synopsis The range of a binary relation.
Function set[&T1] range (rel[&T0,&T1] R)
Description Returns the range (i.e., second element of each tuple) of binary relation R
Examples 
rascal>import Relation;
ok
rascal>range({<1,10>, <2,20>});
set[int]: {10,20}
rascal>range({<"mon", 1>, <"tue", 2>});
set[int]: {2,1}
